rag Installation Guide

BASIC INSTALLATION

Prerequestites:
 - GNU Emacs version >= 26.2 (tested on 32.0.50).
 - Posix makefile runner (tested with GNU Make).
 - rustc vresion >= 1.97.0 (tested on 1.98.0).

Compiling:
  1.  Invoke the 'configure' script:

		 ./configure

  2.  Invoke the 'make' program:

         make

  3.  Install

         make install

      You may want to change the directory that gets installed into.

         # Replace /usr/local with directory that contains share/emacs/site-lisp
         make install PREFIX=/usr/local

         # Or configure the directories
         make install SITELISP=/usr/local/share/emacs/site-lisp
         # ${PREFIX}/lib/emacs is not part of emacs by default but this path
         # would follow hier(7).
         make install LIBDIR=/usr/local/lib/emacs

     Alternatively you can just add the directories at the command-line.

         emacs -L lisp -L target/release
